# Cursor Project Rules

# Structure
- Use TypeScript whenever possible.
- Keep each module small and composable.
- Separate LLM prompts into PROMPTS.md.
- All Cloudflare-specific components must comply with Workers runtime.

# Code Style
- No +page.server.ts style frameworks.
- Use clean async/await patterns.
- No third-party dependencies unless absolutely necessary.

# Worker Rules
- All Worker code must be isomorphic (no Node-specific APIs).
- Use fetch() instead of Axios.
- Do not use fs or path.

# Durable Objects
- Keep DO state JSON-serializable.
- Provide getState() and updateState() helper functions.

# Realtime / Pages
- Keep frontend vanilla HTML/CSS/JS.
- No React required for MVP.

# Testing / Logs
- Use console.log for debugging.
- Never leak API keys.

# Goals
- Produce a deployable Cloudflare AI agent with:
  - memory
  - workflows
  - UI